		<p>Nutsy Bolts is a multi-player browser game of fun, randomness, absurdity, and awesomesauce.  What more need be said?</p> 
		
		<p>Nutsy Bolts is the brainchild of Mark Goetz, who is the designer, programmer, maintainer, benevolent dictator, and all-around awesome guy behind it.  Mark would also like to thank those who suffered the indignity of testing its early stages, including (but not limited to) Chad Behnke, Liz Blankenship, Michelle Cummings, Orin Davis, Michelle Davis, Katie Dover-Taylor, Melissa Fichter, Jackie Frank, Joel Frank, Josh Gerrish, Leanna Gingras, Kurt Goetz, Alex Goldman, James Lauser, Sarah Lauser, Noah Liebman, Becky Lieberman, Ted Liu, Andrea McVittie, Dan Menna, Brenda Salem, Tova Searleman, John Theiss, and Lauren Wendel.  I'd also like to thank <a href="http://hosting.jlauser.net/" target="_blank">jlauser.net hosting</a> for hosting the site.
		
